item.title: CVE-2016-9257|2024-08-06T02:42:11.282Z -- f5%20networks%2C%20inc. -- big-ip%20apm
item.description: In F5 BIG-IP APM 12.0.0 through 12.1.2, non-authenticated users may be able to inject JavaScript into a request that will then be rendered and executed in the context of the Administrative user when the Administrative user is viewing the Access System Logs, allowing the non-authenticated user to carry out a Cross Site Scripting (XSS) attack against the Administrative user.
